            "body": "Hi @justinmk,\r\n\r\nHopefully, this Gif, better illustrates the issue that I'm facing and why I'm thinking it's a bug.\r\n\r\n![nvim-lua-glitch](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/16037346/207295087-4b5cc1b9-4488-49c4-a3b2-66ddaa73b594.gif)\r\n\r\nMy expectation came more from the use of `:!>&2 echo \"error\"`, here the text `error` is redirected to `stderr` and further appended to the `:messages`.\r\n\r\nThanks, for taking a look at this issue and please let me know, whether I could somehow illustrate it in another (maybe better) way.",
